{"questionId":"21321","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The price of gas at Leon’s gas station is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>50</mn></math>&nbsp;per litre. If a customer buys a minimum of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> litres, a discount of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mn>5</mn></math> is applied.</p>\n<p>This can be modelled by the following function, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>, which gives the total cost when buying&nbsp;a minimum of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> litres at Leon’s gas station.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>50</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>10</mn></math></p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> is the number of litres of gas that a customer buys.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>L</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>(</mo><mn>70</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>70</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>50</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>50</mn></math>&nbsp;litres&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21321","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.4b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find L-1(70).","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.2—Functions, notation domain, range and inverse as reflection","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}